<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 28 at 12:20PM CST  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Band of Heavy Snow...
At noon, Doppler radar and surface observations showed a 15 mile
wide band of heavy snow from Dubuque Iowa to east of Moline
Illinois. This band of snow was moving east and will move across
northwest Illinois early this afternoon.
Visibilities will be greatly reduced to about 1/4 mile in this
snow band with snowfall rates more than an inch an hour.
Roads, bridges and overpasses will be slick and hazardous with
the snow and ice accumulations. Be extra cautious on bridges and
overpasses.</description>
